        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37380",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bate",
                        "name": "bate",
                        "displayName": "Marco Kaiser",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What document type do you use?\r\n\r\n\r\nBtw. IE6 sucks and should not be supported in any way.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bate",
                        "name": "bate",
                        "displayName": "Marco Kaiser",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-05T01:47:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-05T01:47:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37385",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "name": "jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "displayName": "Jon Gilbert",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree that IE6 sucks, but that's another story ;-) Document type is XHTML 1.0 Transitional but that should also be irrelevant. In the current output the label includes the element it is labelling which seems to me to be semantically wrong. There's a simple example on http:\/\/www.w3schools.com\/tags\/tag_label.asp - it is irrelevant where the label is in relation to the radio button, but they should be two distinct elements, not nested.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "name": "jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "displayName": "Jon Gilbert",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-05T03:01:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-05T03:01:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37388",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bate",
                        "name": "bate",
                        "displayName": "Marco Kaiser",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The Label helper produces different html for different doctypes. Do you use in your layout\/view the $this->doctype() helper?\r\nIf not try with. I think this isnt a bug. :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bate",
                        "name": "bate",
                        "displayName": "Marco Kaiser",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-05T03:10:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-05T03:10:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37391",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "name": "jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "displayName": "Jon Gilbert",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Doctype is hardcoded in the layout template, but I disagree that this is relevant. doctype affects the closing tag:\r\n\r\n        $endTag = ' \/>';\r\n        if (($this->view instanceof Zend_View_Abstract) && !$this->view->doctype()->isXhtml()) {\r\n            $endTag= '>';\r\n        }\r\n\r\nbut building the button and label does not depend on it:\r\n            \/\/ Wrap the radios in labels\r\n            $radio = '<label'\r\n                    . $this->_htmlAttribs($label_attribs) . ' for=\"' . $optId . '\">'\r\n                    . (('prepend' == $labelPlacement) ? $opt_label : '')\r\n                    . '<input type=\"' . $this->_inputType . '\"'\r\n                    . ' name=\"' . $name . '\"'\r\n                    . ' id=\"' . $optId . '\"'\r\n                    . ' value=\"' . $this->view->escape($opt_value) . '\"'\r\n                    . $checked\r\n                    . $disabled\r\n                    . $this->_htmlAttribs($attribs)\r\n                    . $endTag\r\n                    . (('append' == $labelPlacement) ? $opt_label : '')\r\n                    . '<\/label>';\r\n\r\nHowever, I agree that $labelPlacement is actually irrelevant - not sure what I was thinking about there ;-) The code that actually needs fixing is the above definition of $radio. Here's my solution:\r\n\r\n            \/\/ create radio button and label and put them together in the required order\r\n            $label = '<label'\r\n                    . $this->_htmlAttribs($label_attribs) . ' for=\"' . $optId . '\">'\r\n                    . $opt_label\r\n                    . '<\/label>';\r\n            $radio =  '<input type=\"' . $this->_inputType . '\"'\r\n                    . ' name=\"' . $name . '\"'\r\n                    . ' id=\"' . $optId . '\"'\r\n                    . ' value=\"' . $this->view->escape($opt_value) . '\"'\r\n                    . $checked\r\n                    . $disabled\r\n                    . $this->_htmlAttribs($attribs)\r\n                    . $endTag;\r\n            if ('prepend' == $labelPlacement) {\r\n                $radio = $label . $radio;\r\n            } else {\r\n                $radio .= $label;\r\n            }\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "name": "jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "displayName": "Jon Gilbert",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-05T07:17:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-05T07:17:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41708",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jfm",
                        "name": "jfm",
                        "displayName": "James Boykin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes this bug makes it difficult to use many jquery plugins. Would love to see this fixed! Manual patching for now...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jfm",
                        "name": "jfm",
                        "displayName": "James Boykin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-24T15:59:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-24T15:59:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42022",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ihwan",
                        "name": "ihwan",
                        "displayName": "Kim Hwan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This bug makes it difficult to use many jquery plugins. \r\nFor example, jquery ui radio buttons has this problem.  http:\/\/jqueryui.com\/demos\/button\/radio.html",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ihwan",
                        "name": "ihwan",
                        "displayName": "Kim Hwan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-08-20T03:30:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-08-20T03:30:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44673",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=daniel.zahariev",
                        "name": "daniel.zahariev",
                        "displayName": "Daniel Zahariev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi all, i had the same issue with this in terms of jQuery usage and used the following code for reordering:\r\n$('input[type=\"radio\"]', 'some scope').each(function(){\r\n  var radio = $(this), label = elem.parent();\r\n  radio.detach();\r\n  label.before(radio);\r\n});\r\nHope this helps someone.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=daniel.zahariev",
                        "name": "daniel.zahariev",
                        "displayName": "Daniel Zahariev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-08T02:50:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-08T02:50:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44675",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please read the HTML specification carefully! This is valid HTML and XHTML! \r\nThese are \"implicit labels\": [HTML 4: 17 Forms - 17.9.1 The LABEL element|http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/html401\/interact\/forms.html#h-17.9.1]",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-08T04:10:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-08T04:10:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45460",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "name": "jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "displayName": "Jon Gilbert",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "No, those aren't implicit labels. Implicit labels don't have a \"for\" attribute - that makes them explicit",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "name": "jon.gilbert@net-entwicklung.de",
                        "displayName": "Jon Gilbert",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-08T23:54:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-08T23:54:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45461",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}No, those aren't implicit labels. Implicit labels don't have a \"for\" attribute - that makes them explicit{quote}\r\nRight! The \"for\" attribute is not needed and makes here also no sense.\r\n\r\n{code:title=Excerpt from Zend_View_Helper_FormRadio}\r\n\/\/ Wrap the radios in labels\r\n$radio = '<label'\r\n        . $this->_htmlAttribs($label_attribs) . ' for=\"' . $optId . '\">' \/\/ \"for\" can be removed!\r\n        . (('prepend' == $labelPlacement) ? $opt_label : '')\r\n        . '<input type=\"' . $this->_inputType . '\"'\r\n        . ' name=\"' . $name . '\"'\r\n        . ' id=\"' . $optId . '\"'\r\n        . ' value=\"' . $this->view->escape($opt_value) . '\"'\r\n        . $checked\r\n        . $disabled\r\n        . $this->_htmlAttribs($attribs)\r\n        . $endTag\r\n        . (('append' == $labelPlacement) ? $opt_label : '')\r\n        . '<\/label>';\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n[HTML 4: 17 Forms - 17.9.1 The LABEL element - for|http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/html4\/interact\/forms.html#adef-for]",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-09T02:33:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-09T02:33:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50561",
                    "author": {
